<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,745,626,652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—This species is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1101,1215,626,652]" name="Argentina" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1229,1328,627,653]" name="Uruguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1342,1447,627,653]" name="Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,218,662,688]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[281,349,662,688]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Krapovickas, A." box="[368,595,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="209 - 253" refId="ref19538" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2007 b) Las especies de Sida secc. Malacroideae (Malvaceae) del Cono Sur de Sudamerica. Bonplandia 16: 209 - 253. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 163 - 4150" type="journal article" year="2007">Krapovickas 2007b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[611,844,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis box="[714,774,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alverson, W. S. &amp; Michel, L. R. C. de &amp; Dorr, L. J. &amp; Fryxell, P. A. &amp; Krapovickas, A. &amp; Meneses, Q. R. I." box="[858,1102,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="786 - 819" refId="ref17710" refString="Alverson, W. S., Michel, L. R. C. de, Dorr, L. J., Fryxell, P. A., Krapovickas, A. &amp; Meneses, Q. R. I. (2014) Malvaceae. In: Jorgensen, P. M., Nee, M. H. &amp; Beck, S. G. (Eds.) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares de Bolivia, Monographs in systematic botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden. Missouri Botanical Garden Press., St. Louis, pp. 786 - 819." type="book chapter" year="2014">
Alverson 
<emphasis box="[971,1032,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1117,1265,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). For 
<collectingCountry box="[1338,1406,662,688]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Brazil</collectingCountry>
the species is known from 
<collectingRegion box="[395,543,698,725]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[555,780,698,725]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[835,1044,698,724]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
states (
<bibRefCitation author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1129,1275,698,724]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In the latter, it occurs only in southwest region in Park grassland and Shallow soil grassland (
<figureCitation box="[1025,1125,734,760]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[262,1350,253,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[199,1389,190,1947]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of Sida anomala, S. cerradoensis, S. confusa, S. cordifolia, S. dubia, S. farroupilhensis and S. lonchitis in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415491/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[1300,1452,734,760]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref19221" refString="IUCN (2017) Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 13. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommitttee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 3 November 2019)" type="url" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, the species is Least Concern (LC) with an Extent of Occurrence (EOO) of 1,095,931.709 Km² and an Area of Occupancy of 220 Km². Furthermore, it does not meet the criterion B(b) and B(c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
